  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Senator George Turner evidently\ndoes not think that the opening of\nfriendly relations between the Ca\nmadam Pacific and the Great Northern\nwill stop plans for the Kootenai\nbranch to Spokane.\n\n\nHe intends to return to Spokane\nwithin a week or 10 days to forward\nthe work of laying out the road and\ncomplete the company's organization.\n\n\nA field force of engineers will prob\nably begin work the first of the open\nseason."
    }
